  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Denmark/Ghana Partnership with Global Financial Integrity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global Financial Integrity (GFI) and the Government of Denmark (Denmark) are partnering with the Government of the Republic of Ghana (Government), in coordination with the Minister of Finance and the Governor of the Central Bank of Ghana, to do an in-depth study of unrecorded financial flows in Ghana stemming from trade misinvoicing. The project will be financed by the Government of Denmark in alignment with its action plan on tax, development and financial transparency. Following on from the study, GFI will also assist a team of senior officials from the Government of Ghana to review, discuss and suggest modifications to existing policies, regulations and laws and design new policies to curtail unrecorded flows in Ghana due to trade misinvoicing, as identified in GFI&#xBF;s economic analysis.</narrative>
  </description>
